The SCaLE AV Cutter segments multi-hour YouTube live streams into individual videos
for posting to the
https://www.youtube.com/@socallinuxexpo[SCaLE YouTube channel].

During SCaLE, rooms are streamed in continuous 6–10 hour blocks to minimize
technical failure points. Because YouTube Studio is limited to videos under 2 hours,
the Cutter is necessary to process these extended recordings.

=== Before You Begin

[WARNING]
====
*The Cutter cannot handle simultaneous edits.* If two users edit the same room or
talk simultaneously, the last user to submit will overwrite all previous work.

Work together to explicitly assign distinct rooms to editors and reviewers before
starting — e.g., Editor A handles "Ballroom A," Editor B handles "Ballroom H."
====

=== User Roles

Volunteers access the Cutter as one of three roles. The system operates on a
*high-trust model* using shared passwords rather than individual accounts.

[cols="1,3", options="header"]
|===
|Role |Responsibilities

|*Editor*
|Identifies start and end of talks, selects thumbnails, adds metadata, and assesses
whether footage is usable. Moves talks from null state → *Needs Review*.

|*Reviewer*
|Performs quality assurance on Editor work and confirms the video is ready for upload.
Moves talks from *Needs Review* → final state.

|*Admin*
|Highest level of access.
|===
